{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17526874","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17526874"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-29T15:27:00+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-29T15:27:00+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"14164"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"14164","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/14164"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.24,0.22,0.49,0.05,0.01]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"6847"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"58389"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"6847","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/6847"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"14164"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"43811"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"24"},{"type":"tags","id":"26"},{"type":"tags","id":"64"},{"type":"tags","id":"72"},{"type":"tags","id":"78"},{"type":"tags","id":"687"},{"type":"tags","id":"1051"},{"type":"tags","id":"1052"},{"type":"tags","id":"1674"},{"type":"tags","id":"2356"},{"type":"tags","id":"3049"},{"type":"tags","id":"3572"},{"type":"tags","id":"4623"},{"type":"tags","id":"4961"},{"type":"tags","id":"4971"},{"type":"tags","id":"4987"},{"type":"tags","id":"5967"},{"type":"tags","id":"11630"},{"type":"tags","id":"11632"},{"type":"tags","id":"11650"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"15539"},{"type":"contributions","id":"17732"},{"type":"contributions","id":"18214"},{"type":"contributions","id":"44720"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"58389","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/58389"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EAn 18-year-old woman is brought to the Emergency Department by her parent after admitting to taking a polypharmacy overdose at home. Her parent isn\u0027t sure which drugs she took or in what quantities, but knows she had access to the following prescription and over-the-counter medications: oxycodone, temazepam, verapamil, atorvastatin, ibuprofen, and paracetamol.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EOn examination, she appears drowsy but responsive. Her pulse rate is 45/min, blood pressure 75/40 mmHg, respiratory rate 14/min, and SpO2 95% on room air. She is nauseated with occasional vomiting.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following medications is most likely responsible for her deranged vital signs?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Oxycodone","Temazepam","Verapamil","Paracetamol","Ibuprofen"],"correctOptions":[2],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThis patient presents with profound bradycardia and hypotension, which are hallmark features of calcium channel blocker toxicity. \u003Cstrong\u003EVerapamil\u003C/strong\u003E overdose causes these effects through blockade of L-type calcium channels in cardiac and vascular smooth muscle, leading to decreased cardiac contractility and peripheral vasodilation.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EOxycodone\u003C/strong\u003E overdose typically causes respiratory depression, pinpoint pupils, and decreased consciousness. While it can cause hypotension, it does not typically cause significant bradycardia.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ETemazepam\u003C/strong\u003E and other benzodiazepines primarily cause central nervous system depression. While they may contribute to hypotension, they rarely cause the degree of cardiovascular compromise seen here.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EParacetamol\u003C/strong\u003E overdose is initially asymptomatic and later causes hepatotoxicity. It does not cause acute cardiovascular collapse.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EIbuprofen\u003C/strong\u003E overdose typically causes gastrointestinal symptoms and rarely causes significant cardiovascular effects unless taken in massive quantities.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003ETreatment of calcium channel blocker overdose includes calcium administration, high-dose insulin therapy, and vasopressor support. The use of high-dose insulin (1 unit/kg/hour) improves cardiac contractility and vascular tone by enhancing myocardial glucose uptake and utilisation.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":null,"learningPoints":["Calcium channel blocker overdose characteristically presents with bradycardia and hypotension.","High dose insulin therapy is an effective treatment for calcium channel blocker overdose.","Other medications commonly involved in overdose (opioids, benzodiazepines, NSAIDs) do not typically cause profound bradycardia."],"references":["Alshaya OA, Alhamed A, Althewaibi S, Fetyani L, Alshehri S, Alnashmi F, Alharbi S, Alrashed M, Alqifari SF, Alshaya AI. Calcium Channel Blocker Toxicity: A Practical Approach. J Multidiscip Healthc. 2022 Aug 30;15:1851-1862. doi: 10.2147/JMDH.S374887. PMID: 36065348; PMCID: PMC9440664. Available at: https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC9440664/"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"43811"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"14164"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"43811","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/43811"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-10-31T15:04:29+10:30","updatedAt":"2024-10-31T15:06:57+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"6847"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"58389"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"24","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/24"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83d\ude91","name":"Emergency Medicine","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":